# Readme file to help you to execute this script			#
#						 			#
#########################################################################


Prerequisites : 
- centos 6.x - 64 bit
- /etc/hosts entries should be present if you dont have dns setup
- ssh should be configured on default port on each host
- "compose" user should be present on each host

Step 1: Clone shell-assignment directory on your system from which you are going to run this script

Step 2: inside script specify all your hosts on following line

line number 6 : hosts=

Step 3: execute the script with ./ssh-hosts.sh command and give "yes" answer to each question.
You have to provide password for ssh keys verification
